{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775888179745,"sessionID":"ses_284d2baf2ffeA74L7nXmd4nVre","part":{"id":"prt_d7b2dbe49001wINFbgHcJNDGOM","messageID":"msg_d7b2db1a40017qEtlJeFOq8rEQ","sessionID":"ses_284d2baf2ffeA74L7nXmd4nVre","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_a242372b158f4b658497147b","state":{"status":"error","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler/design.md","content":"# Unit Test Implementation Design - pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler\n\n## Overview\n\nThis document describes the technical implementation plan for comprehensive unit tests for the `pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler` module. The reconciler module contains Kubernetes controller logic for managing AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter resources.\n\n## Module Architecture\n\n### Core Components\n\n1. **ControllerManager** (`manager.go:44-152`)\n   - Lifecycle management for reconcilers\n   - Event recorder setup\n   - Client initialization (dynamic + kubernetes)\n\n2. **AgentRuntimeReconciler** (`agentruntime_reconciler.go:23-319`)\n   - Main reconciliation logic for AgentRuntime resources\n   - Pod lifecycle management\n   - Work queue processing\n\n3. **SandboxProcessor** (`sandbox_processor.go:32-299`)\n   - Pod specification building\n   - Update detection logic\n   - Pod recreation strategy\n\n4. **StatusUpdater** (`status_updater.go:18-200`)\n   - Status synchronization between pods and custom resources\n   - Condition building from pod status\n\n5. **Utility Components**\n   - `owner_reference.go`: Owner reference and finalizer management\n   - `errors.go`: Reconcile error types and retry logic\n   - `metrics.go`: Reconciliation metrics tracking\n   - `interface.go`: Common interfaces and queue operations\n\n## Test Strategy\n\n### Testing Principles\n\n1. **Table-Driven Tests**: Use table-driven test patterns for coverage of multiple scenarios\n2. **Mock-Based Isolation**: Use fake clients and mocks to isolate unit under test\n3. **Behavior Verification**: Verify state changes and side effects\n4. **Edge Case Coverage**: Test error conditions, timeouts, and boundary values\n\n### Test Categories\n\n#### 1. ControllerManager Tests\n\n**File**: `manager_test.go`\n\n**Test Coverage**:\n\n```go\n// Constructor tests\n- TestNewControllerManager_Success\n- TestNewControllerManager_InvalidConfig\n\n// Lifecycle tests\n- TestControllerManager_AddReconciler\n- TestControllerManager_Start\n- TestControllerManager_Shutdown\n\n// Client accessor tests\n- TestControllerManager_GetDynamicClient\n- TestControllerManager_GetK8sClient\n- TestControllerManager_GetRecorder\n\n// Utility function tests\n- TestCalculateBackoff_BasicCases\n- TestCalculateBackoff_ExponentialGrowth\n- TestCalculateBackoff_MaxCap\n- TestCalculateBackoff_Jitter\n- TestMapObjectReference\n```\n\n**Implementation Pattern**:\n\n```go\nfunc TestCalculateBackoff_BasicCases(t *testing.T) {\n    tests := []struct {\n        name       string\n        retryCount int\n        minDelay   time.Duration\n        maxDelay   time.Duration\n    }{\n        {\"first retry\", 0, 1 * time.Second, 2 * time.Second},\n        {\"second retry\", 1, 2 * time.Second, 4 * time.Second},\n        {\"max cap\", 10, 5 * time.Minute, 5 * time.Minute},\n    }\n\n    for _, tt := range tests {\n        t.Run(tt.name, func(t *testing.T) {\n            delay := CalculateBackoff(tt.retryCount)\n            assert.GreaterOrEqual(t, delay, tt.minDelay)\n            assert.LessOrEqual(t, delay, tt.maxDelay)\n        })\n    }\n}\n```\n\n#### 2. AgentRuntimeReconciler Tests\n\n**File**: `agentruntime_reconciler_test.go`\n\n**Test Coverage**:\n\n```go\n// Reconciliation flow tests\n- TestReconcile_ResourceNotFound\n- TestReconcile_ResourceBeingDeleted\n- TestReconcile_PodCreation_Success\n- TestReconcile_PodCreation_Failure\n- TestReconcile_PodUpdate_Required\n- TestReconcile_PodUpdate_NotRequired\n- TestReconcile_StatusUpdate_Failure\n\n// Work queue processing tests\n- TestProcessNextWorkItem_Success\n- TestProcessNextWorkItem_Error_Retryable\n- TestProcessNextWorkItem_Error_NonRetryable\n- TestProcessNextWorkItem_Shutdown\n\n// Event enqueueing tests\n- TestEnqueueAgentRuntime\n- TestEnqueueUpdate_ResourceVersionChanged\n- TestEnqueueUpdate_ResourceVersionUnchanged\n- TestEnqueueDelete\n- TestEnqueueOwnedPod\n- TestEnqueueOwnedPodDelete\n\n// Helper method tests\n- TestGetAgentRuntime_Exists\n- TestGetAgentRuntime_NotFound\n- TestGetSandboxPod_Exists\n- TestGetSandboxPod_NotFound\n- TestGetSandboxPod_SelectorFallback\n```\n\n**Mock Setup**:\n\n```go\nfunc newTestAgentRuntimeReconciler(t *testing.T) (*AgentRuntimeReconciler, *fakeClients) {\n    scheme := runtime.NewScheme()\n    _ = corev1.AddToScheme(scheme)\n    _ = runtimev1alpha1.AddToScheme(scheme)\n\n    // Fake dynamic client\n    dynamicClient := fakeDynamicClient.NewSimpleDynamicClient(scheme)\n    \n    // Fake kubernetes client\n    k8sClient := fakeclientset.NewSimpleClientset()\n    \n    // Pod informer setup\n    podInformer := informers.NewSharedInformerFactory(k8sClient, 0).Core().V1().Pods()\n    podLister := podInformer.Lister()\n    podIndexer := podInformer.Informer().GetIndexer()\n\n    // Metrics and config\n    metrics := NewReconcilerMetrics()\n    config := DefaultReconcilerConfig()\n\n    // Event recorder\n    eventBroadcaster := record.NewBroadcaster()\n    recorder := eventBroadcaster.NewRecorder(scheme, corev1.EventSource{\n        Component: \"test-reconciler\",\n    })\n\n    reconciler := NewAgentRuntimeReconciler(\n        dynamicClient,\n        k8sClient,\n        podLister,\n        podIndexer,\n        recorder,\n        metrics,\n        config,\n    )\n\n    return reconciler, &fakeClients{\n        dynamicClient: dynamicClient,\n        k8sClient:     k8sClient,\n    }\n}\n```\n\n#### 3. SandboxProcessor Tests\n\n**File**: `sandbox_processor_test.go` (existing - extend coverage)\n\n**Additional Test Coverage**:\n\n```go\n// Pod building tests\n- TestBuildSandboxPod_BasicLabels\n- TestBuildSandboxPod_CustomLabels\n- TestBuildSandboxPod_Annotations\n- TestBuildSandboxPod_ResourceQuotas\n- TestBuildSandboxPod_NetworkPolicy_Ports\n- TestBuildSandboxPod_CodeInterpreter_Enabled\n- TestBuildSandboxPod_CodeInterpreter_Disabled\n- TestBuildSandboxPod_OwnerReference\n\n// Update detection tests\n- TestNeedsUpdate_ImageChanged\n- TestNeedsUpdate_ResourcesChanged\n- TestNeedsUpdate_EnvChanged\n- TestNeedsUpdate_NoChanges\n- TestNeedsUpdate_EmptyContainers\n\n// Update operation tests\n- TestUpdateSandboxPod_DeleteAndRecreate\n- TestUpdateSandboxPod_DeleteFailure\n- TestUpdateSandboxPod_CreateFailure\n\n// CodeInterpreter pod tests\n- TestBuildCodeInterpreterPod\n- TestNeedsUpdateCodeInterpreter\n- TestUpdateCodeInterpreterPod\n```\n\n**Test Data Builders**:\n\n```go\nfunc newAgentRuntimeBuilder() *agentRuntimeBuilder {\n    return &agentRuntimeBuilder{\n        ar: &runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime{\n            ObjectMeta: metav1.ObjectMeta{\n                Name:      \"test-ar\",\n                Namespace: \"default\",\n            },\n            Spec: runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeSpec{\n                Container: &runtimev1alpha1.ContainerSpec{\n                    Image: \"test-image:latest\",\n                },\n            },\n        },\n    }\n}\n\ntype agentRuntimeBuilder struct {\n    ar *runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime\n}\n\nfunc (b *agentRuntimeBuilder) WithImage(image string) *agentRuntimeBuilder {\n    b.ar.Spec.Container.Image = image\n    return b\n}\n\nfunc (b *agentRuntimeBuilder) WithResources(cpu, memory string) *agentRuntimeBuilder {\n    b.ar.Spec.Resources = &runtimev1alpha1.ResourceQuota{\n        CPU:    cpu,\n        Memory: memory,\n    }\n    return b\n}\n\nfunc (b *agentRuntimeBuilder) Build() *runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime {\n    return b.ar.DeepCopy()\n}\n```\n\n#### 4. StatusUpdater Tests\n\n**File**: `status_updater_test.go`\n\n**Test Coverage**:\n\n```go\n// Status update tests\n- TestUpdateAgentRuntimeStatus_PodNil\n- TestUpdateAgentRuntimeStatus_PodRunning\n- TestUpdateAgentRuntimeStatus_PodPending\n- TestUpdateAgentRuntimeStatus_PodFailed\n- TestUpdateAgentRuntimeStatus_NoChange_SkipUpdate\n- TestUpdateAgentRuntimeStatus_SandboxRef_Set\n- TestUpdateAgentRuntimeStatus_Conditions_FromPod\n\n// CodeInterpreter status tests\n- TestUpdateCodeInterpreterStatus_PodNil\n- TestUpdateCodeInterpreterStatus_PodRunning\n- TestUpdateCodeInterpreterStatus_NoChange\n\n// Helper function tests\n- TestMapPodPhaseToRuntimePhase_Pending\n- TestMapPodPhaseToRuntimePhase_Running\n- TestMapPodPhaseToRuntimePhase_Failed\n- TestMapPodPhaseToRuntimePhase_Succeeded\n- TestMapPodPhaseToRuntimePhase_Unknown\n- TestBuildConditionsFromPod\n```\n\n**Status Verification**:\n\n```go\nfunc TestUpdateAgentRuntimeStatus_PodRunning(t *testing.T) {\n    ctx := context.Background()\n    reconciler, clients := newTestStatusUpdater()\n\n    ar := newAgentRuntimeBuilder().Build()\n    pod := newPodBuilder().\n        WithName(\"sandbox-test-ar\").\n        WithPhase(corev1.PodRunning).\n        WithStartTime(metav1.Now()).\n        Build()\n\n    // Create pod in fake client\n    _, _ = clients.k8sClient.CoreV1().Pods(ar.Namespace).Create(ctx, pod, metav1.CreateOptions{})\n\n    err := reconciler.UpdateAgentRuntimeStatus(ctx, ar, pod)\n    assert.NoError(t, err)\n\n    // Verify status was updated\n    assert.Equal(t, runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimePhaseRunning, ar.Status.Phase)\n    assert.NotNil(t, ar.Status.SandboxRef)\n    assert.Equal(t, pod.Name, ar.Status.SandboxRef.Name)\n}\n```\n\n#### 5. Owner Reference Tests\n\n**File**: `owner_reference_test.go`\n\n**Test Coverage**:\n\n```go\n// Owner reference management tests\n- TestSetControllerReference\n- TestSetControllerReference_MultipleOwners\n- TestIsOwnedBy_True\n- TestIsOwnedBy_False\n- TestGetControllerUID\n- TestHasOwnerReference\n- TestAddOwnerReference\n- TestRemoveOwnerReference\n\n// Finalizer management tests\n- TestHasFinalizer_Exists\n- TestHasFinalizer_NotExists\n- TestAddFinalizer\n- TestRemoveFinalizer\n- TestIsBeingDeleted\n- TestIsReadyToCleanup\n\n// Reference comparison tests\n- TestIsOwnerReferenceEqual\n- TestBuildOwnerReference\n- TestNewOwnerReference\n```\n\n#### 6. Error Handling Tests\n\n**File**: `errors_test.go`\n\n**Test Coverage**:\n\n```go\n// Error type tests\n- TestReconcileError_Error\n- TestReconcileError_Unwrap\n\n// Retry logic tests\n- TestIsRetryableError_ReconcileError_Retryable\n- TestIsRetryableError_ReconcileError_NonRetryable\n- TestIsRetryableError_K8sTimeout\n- TestIsRetryableError_K8sTooManyRequests\n- TestIsRetryableError_K8sServerTimeout\n- TestIsRetryableError_OtherError\n\n// Error constructor tests\n- TestNewReconcileError\n```\n\n#### 7. Metrics Tests\n\n**File**: `metrics_test.go` (extend existing coverage)\n\n**Test Coverage**:\n\n```go\n// Metrics recording tests\n- TestObserveReconcileDuration\n- TestRecordError\n- TestRecordReconcile\n- TestGetReconcileCount\n- TestGetErrorCount\n- TestGetAverageReconcileTime_Zero\n- TestGetAverageReconcileTime_WithSamples\n\n// NoOp metrics tests\n- TestNoOpMetrics_NoPanic\n```\n\n## Data Structures\n\n### Test Fixtures\n\n#### AgentRuntime Fixtures\n\n```go\n// Minimal valid AgentRuntime\nfunc minimalAgentRuntime() *runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime {\n    return &runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime{\n        ObjectMeta: metav1.ObjectMeta{\n            Name:      \"test\",\n            Namespace: \"default\",\n            UID:       types.UID(\"test-uid\"),\n        },\n        Spec: runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeSpec{\n            Container: &runtimev1alpha1.ContainerSpec{\n                Image: \"nginx:latest\",\n            },\n        },\n    }\n}\n\n// AgentRuntime with full spec\nfunc fullAgentRuntime() *runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime {\n    return &runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime{\n        ObjectMeta: metav1.ObjectMeta{\n            Name:      \"full-test\",\n            Namespace: \"default\",\n            UID:       types.UID(\"full-uid\"),\n            Labels: map[string]string{\n                \"app\": \"test\",\n            },\n            Annotations: map[string]string{\n                \"description\": \"test runtime\",\n            },\n        },\n        Spec: runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeSpec{\n            Container: &runtimev1alpha1.ContainerSpec{\n                Image:   \"nginx:latest\",\n                Command: []string{\"/bin/sh\"},\n                Args:    []string{\"-c\", \"echo hello\"},\n                Env: []corev1.EnvVar{\n                    {Name: \"ENV1\", Value: \"val1\"},\n                },\n            },\n            Resources: &runtimev1alpha1.ResourceQuota{\n                CPU:    \"100m\",\n                Memory: \"128Mi\",\n            },\n            Network: &runtimev1alpha1.NetworkPolicy{\n                IngressRules: []runtimev1alpha1.IngressRule{\n                    {Ports: []int32{8080, 9090}},\n                },\n            },\n            CodeInterpreter: &runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreterSpec{\n                Enabled: true,\n                Image:   \"python:3.9\",\n            },\n        },\n    }\n}\n```\n\n#### Pod Fixtures\n\n```go\n// Sandbox pod fixture\nfunc sandboxPod(arName, namespace string, phase corev1.PodPhase) *corev1.Pod {\n    return &corev1.Pod{\n        ObjectMeta: metav1.ObjectMeta{\n            Name:      fmt.Sprintf(\"sandbox-%s\", arName),\n            Namespace: namespace,\n            Labels: map[string]string{\n                \"app.kubernetes.io/name\":       \"agentcube\",\n                \"agentcube.volcano.sh/runtime\": arName,\n            },\n            OwnerReferences: []metav1.OwnerReference{\n                {\n                    APIVersion: \"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1\",\n                    Kind:       \"AgentRuntime\",\n                    Name:       arName,\n                    UID:        types.UID(fmt.Sprintf(\"%s-uid\", arName)),\n                    Controller: boolPtr(true),\n                },\n            },\n        },\n        Status: corev1.PodStatus{\n            Phase: phase,\n            Conditions: []corev1.PodCondition{\n                {Type: corev1.PodReady, Status: corev1.ConditionTrue},\n            },\n        },\n    }\n}\n```\n\n### Fake Client Setup\n\n```go\ntype fakeClients struct {\n    dynamicClient  *fakeDynamicClient.FakeDynamicClient\n    k8sClient      *fakeclientset.Clientset\n    podInformer    cache.SharedIndexInformer\n    podLister      corev1lister.PodLister\n    eventRecorder  record.EventRecorder\n}\n\nfunc newFakeClients(objects ...runtime.Object) *fakeClients {\n    scheme := runtime.NewScheme()\n    _ = corev1.AddToScheme(scheme)\n    _ = runtimev1alpha1.AddToScheme(scheme)\n\n    k8sClient := fakeclientset.NewSimpleClientset(objects...)\n    dynamicClient := fakeDynamicClient.NewSimpleDynamicClient(scheme)\n\n    // Setup informer\n    podInformer := informers.NewSharedInformerFactory(k8sClient, 0).\n        Core().V1().Pods().Informer()\n    \n    // Start informer\n    stopCh := make(chan struct{})\n    go podInformer.Run(stopCh)\n    cache.WaitForCacheSync(stopCh, podInformer.HasSynced)\n\n    return &fakeClients{\n        dynamicClient:  dynamicClient,\n        k8sClient:      k8sClient,\n        podInformer:    podInformer,\n    }\n}\n```\n\n## API Contracts\n\n### Reconciler Interface\n\n```go\n// Reconciler interface to be tested\ntype Reconciler interface {\n    Run(ctx context.Context)\n    Reconcile(ctx context.Context, req Request) (Result, error)\n}\n\n// Request structure\ntype Request struct {\n    Namespace string\n    Name      string\n}\n\n// Result structure\ntype Result struct {\n    Requeue      bool\n    RequeueAfter time.Duration\n}\n```\n\n### Expected Behaviors\n\n1. **Reconcile Success**: Returns `Result{Requeue: false}`, `nil` error\n2. **Resource Not Found**: Returns `Result{}`, `nil` error (no requeue)\n3. **Retryable Error**: Returns `Result{RequeueAfter: backoff}`, `nil`\n4. **Non-Retryable Error**: Returns `Result{}`, `error`\n\n## Error Handling Strategy\n\n### Error Classification\n\n```go\n// Retryable errors\n- k8s_errors.IsTimeout\n- k8s_errors.IsTooManyRequests\n- k8s_errors.IsServerTimeout\n- ReconcileError with Retryable=true\n\n// Non-retryable errors\n- k8s_errors.IsNotFound (handled gracefully)\n- k8s_errors.IsInvalid\n- k8s_errors.IsForbidden\n- ReconcileError with Retryable=false\n```\n\n### Error Wrapping Pattern\n\n```go\nfunc TestReconcileError_Unwrap(t *testing.T) {\n    original := errors.New(\"original error\")\n    wrapped := NewReconcileError(\n        ErrPodCreationFailed,\n        \"pod creation failed\",\n        original,\n        true,\n    )\n\n    assert.True(t, errors.Is(wrapped, original))\n    assert.Contains(t, wrapped.Error(), \"PodCreationFailed\")\n    assert.Equal(t, \"original error\", wrapped.Unwrap().Error())\n}\n```\n\n## Testing Tools and Dependencies\n\n### Required Packages\n\n```go\nimport (\n    \"context\"\n    \"testing\"\n    \"time\"\n\n    \"github.com/stretchr/testify/assert\"\n    \"github.com/stretchr/testify/require\"\n    \"go.uber.org/goleak\" // Goroutine leak detection\n\n    corev1 \"k8s.io/api/core/v1\"\n    metav1 \"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1\"\n    \"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime\"\n    \"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/types\"\n    \"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/watch\"\n    \"k8s.io/client-go/dynamic/fake\" as fakeDynamicClient\n    \"k8s.io/client-go/kubernetes/fake\" as fakeclientset\n    \"k8s.io/client-go/testing\" // Action interception\n    \"k8s.io/client-go/tools/cache\"\n    \"k8s.io/client-go/tools/record\"\n    \"k8s.io/client-go/informers\"\n\n    runtimev1alpha1 \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1\"\n)\n```\n\n### Test Utilities\n\n```go\n// Test helper for waiting on conditions\nfunc waitForCondition(t *testing.T, condition func() bool, timeout time.Duration, msg string) {\n    t.Helper()\n    start := time.Now()\n    for time.Since(start) < timeout {\n        if condition() {\n            return\n        }\n        time.Sleep(10 * time.Millisecond)\n    }\n    t.Fatal(msg)\n}\n\n// Test helper for counting actions\nfunc countActions(t *testing.T, actions []testing.Action, verb string) int {\n    t.Helper()\n    count := 0\n    for _, action := range actions {\n        if action.GetVerb() == verb {\n            count++\n        }\n    }\n    return count\n}\n```\n\n## Test Execution Plan\n\n### Phase 1: Foundation Tests\n1. Utility function tests (`owner_reference_test.go`, `errors_test.go`)\n2. Metrics tests (`metrics_test.go`)\n3. Manager tests (`manager_test.go`)\n\n### Phase 2: Core Reconciler Tests\n1. SandboxProcessor tests (extend `sandbox_processor_test.go`)\n2. StatusUpdater tests (`status_updater_test.go`)\n3. AgentRuntimeReconciler tests (`agentruntime_reconciler_test.go`)\n\n### Phase 3: Integration Tests\n1. Full reconciliation loop tests\n2. Concurrent reconciler tests\n3. Event emission verification\n\n## Coverage Goals\n\n| Component | Target Coverage | Priority |\n|-----------|----------------|----------|\n| `manager.go` | 80% | High |\n| `agentruntime_reconciler.go` | 85% | Critical |\n| `sandbox_processor.go` | 90% | Critical |\n| `status_updater.go` | 85% | High |\n| `owner_reference.go` | 95% | Medium |\n| `errors.go` | 100% | Medium |\n| `metrics.go` | 100% | Low |\n| `interface.go` | 80% | Medium |\n\n## Quality Gates\n\n1. **All tests pass**: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler/...`\n2. **No data races**: `go test -race ./pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler/...`\n3. **Coverage threshold**: `go test -cover ./pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler/...`\n4. **No goroutine leaks**: Use `goleak` in test teardown\n5. **Linting**: `golangci-lint run ./pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler/...`\n\n## Example Test File Structure\n\n```\npkg/workloadmanager/reconciler/\n├── agentruntime_reconciler_test.go\n├── manager_test.go\n├── sandbox_processor_test.go     # existing\n├── status_updater_test.go\n├── owner_reference_test.go\n├── errors_test.go\n├── metrics_test.go\n├── interface_test.go\n└── fixtures/\n    └── test_fixtures.go\n```\n"},"error":"You must read file /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler/design.md before overwriting it. Use the Read tool first","time":{"start":1775888179730,"end":1775888179740}}}}
